## Measuring Neighborhood Quality: Tools and Indices

### Neighborhood Environment Walkability Scale (NEWS)

NEWS is a validated instrument assessing residents' perceptions of neighborhood design features related to physical activity, including:

- Residential density
- Land use mix
- Street connectivity
- Infrastructure for walking and cycling
- Neighborhood aesthetics
- Traffic and crime safety
- Neighborhood satisfaction

Multiple versions exist, including abbreviated and youth-specific forms, adapted internationally ([Cerin et al., 2006](https://doi.org/10.1249/01.mss.0000229009.30769.7d)).

### Neighborhood Vulnerability Index

This index combines affluence and disadvantage indicators with social aspects such as racial composition to measure exposure to neighborhood health risks.

- **Findings:** Black Americans, especially Black women, experience higher neighborhood vulnerability due to residential segregation, contributing to health disparities ([Battle, 2020](https://www.publichealthpost.org/research/measuring-neighborhood-vulnerability/)).

